        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 2 at 1:34PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 134 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Pyatt, or 8 miles northwest of Yellville, moving northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pyatt...                          Summit...
Oakland...                        Ozark Regional Airport...
Ozark Isle...                     Eros...
Fawn Park...                      Flippin...
Lakeway...                        Bull Shoals State Park...
Three Brothers...                 Midway in Baxter County...
Clark Hill...                     Yellville...
Colfax...                         Cotter...
Gassville...                      Bull Shoals...
Fairview in Marion County...      Dodd City...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 400 PM CDT for north central
Arkansas.</instruction>
